      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Video game music can be difficult to strike a good balance with; a balance that is fitting with the genre whilst also being noteworthy enough to stand out. Unfortunately, "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "Healer’s Quest"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " doesn’t have this quality as none of it hooked my attention. It "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "does"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " have a strong fantasy motif that suits the game well and it also keeps a good flow with what is happening on screen. The general combat sound effects come with a bit oomph and casting your spells have a more magical feel to the sound design, however during combat, a lot of these sounds blend in together as they all go off at the same time, leaving things a bit lackluster."
        ]
      ]
